58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AustinPassy/~3/vMlv78TQ8PE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:358:"<p>A Quick tutorial on how to replace the water pump of your old Aerogarden 7 with a new pump.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/">Change the Aerogarden water pump</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://austinpassy.com/?p=2702";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 11 Feb 2013 23:01:09 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7600:"<p>After being stuffed in the corner of my apartment for the last few years I decided to bring out the Aerogarden and start using it again.</p>\n<p>Taking one look at it and I knew that I would have to do some fixes and cleaning. It was heavily calcified and had left over roots from the previous grow cycles.</p>\n<h3>Taking the Aerogarden apart</h3>\n<p>I pulled the bowl off the base and removed the insert. I then flipped the insert over on my cutting sheet (desk protector).</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-001/"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2703" alt="Aerogarden-001" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-001-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>I removed all the screws you see below to separate the two pieces (you&#8217;ll want to do this if you&#8217;ve used the Aerogarden for more than a year or two).</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-002/"><img alt="Aerogarden-002" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-002-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>The bottom piece (the top of the bowl) had quite a bit of calcification left over.</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-003/"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2705" alt="Aerogarden-003" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-003-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>But the real bottom piece or the top of the bowl where the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M5UKNG?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden new water pump">pump</a> dumps the water was totally filled with calcium. Be sure to hose off or thoroughly rinse all that away! I soaked them in water and some calcium and lime remover like CLR.</p>\n<p><em>If you use something like CLR be sure to give it a really good cleaning (you don&#8217;t want any chemicals left over and entering your plants).</em></p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-004/"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2706" alt="Aerogarden-004" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-004-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>Once it&#8217;s clean you&#8217;ll need to flip if over and remove the bottom cap holding in the old water <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M5UKNG?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden new water pump">pump</a>. I used a flat head screwdriver to pry the snaps out. Be gently trying not to break the pieces holding it in.</p>\n\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-005/'' title=''Aerogarden-005''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-005-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Bottom cap need to be removed"/></a>\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-006/'' title=''Aerogarden-006''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-006-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Use a flat head to pry it open"/></a>\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-007/'' title=''Aerogarden-007''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-007-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Clean"/></a>\n\n<h3>Putting it back together again</h3>\n<p>Pull the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M5UKNG?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden new water pump">pump</a> out, being sure to leave the clear plastic hose connection.</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-008/"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2710" alt="Aerogarden-008" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-008-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>Insert the new <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M5UKNG?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden new water pump">pump</a> with the dial facing out and the suction cups facing top (what would be the bottom when flipped over).</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-009.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2711" alt="Aerogarden-009" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-009-1024x682.jpg" width="620" height="412"/></a></p>\n<p>After that you&#8217;ll just have to pop back on the cap, add a <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M45U0K?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden water pump filter">new filter</a> and re-screw on the top and bottom piece.</p>\n\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-010/'' title=''Aerogarden-010''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-010-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Aerogarden-010"/></a>\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-011/'' title=''Aerogarden-011''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-011-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Connecting them back together with screws"/></a>\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-012/'' title=''Aerogarden-012''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-012-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Reattaching the pump connector"/></a>\n\n<p>Finally put the top back into a water filled bowl and connect the unit to test everything out. My new <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://amzn.com/B004M5UKNG?tag=thefro-20" title="Aerogarden new water pump">pump</a> is running and dripping water again!</p>\n\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-013/'' title=''Aerogarden-013''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-013-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Back together"/></a>\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href=''http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/attachment/aerogarden-014/'' title=''Aerogarden-014''><img width="150" height="100" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Aerogarden-014-150x100.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Dripping water again!"/></a>\n\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/change-the-aerogarden-water-pump/">Change the Aerogarden water pump</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/vMlv78TQ8PE" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"New WordPress plugin for Easy Digital Downloads on Extendd";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AustinPassy/~3/nzF8cVjUFyk/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:441:"<p>Yesterday I released a helper plugin to allow users who checkout as a guest register for the site at a later date with the same email used at checkout.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/asides/new-wp-plugin-for-edd-on-extendd/">New WordPress plugin for Easy Digital Downloads on Extendd</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpas