img width="150" height="112" src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_3906-150x112.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Happy 2013"/></a>\n\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/gallery/new-years-eve-in-vegas/">New Years Eve in Vegas</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/9GoOrR_6z2I" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"Introducting Version 7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AustinPassy/~3/BH5JeonyWQw/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:319:"<p>Introducing austinpassy.com Version 7 build on the Hybrid Core framework. </p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/general/introducting-version-7/">Introducting Version 7</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://austinpassy.com/?p=2671";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 27 Dec 2012 19:20:53 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1240:"<p>Well it didn&#8217;t take long to write and design a new WordPress theme for the site. Formally known as <strong>ap7</strong>. Version 6 was just released four months ago, but when you&#8217;ve got some down time over holiday weeks, one tends to want to re-do everything possible. Once again the site is built on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://themehybrid.com/hybrid-core">Hybrid Core</a>.</p>\n<p>If you see some issues/bugs please report them <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/thefrosty/blog/issues">here</a> on github.</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/austinpassy.com-version-7.png"><img src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/austinpassy.com-version-7-1024x688.png" alt="austinpassy.com version 7" width="620" height="416" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2672"/></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/general/introducting-version-7/">Introducting Version 7</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/BH5JeonyWQw" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"Remove Jetpack menu page";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AustinPassy/~3/ELQa7IPLjso/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:361:"<p>Remove the Jetpack menu page for users who can''t "manage_options" or any WordPress role you would like to set.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/remove-jetpack-menu-page/">Remove Jetpack menu page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://austinpassy.com/?p=2663";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Dec 2012 22:00:17 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1346:"<p>I recently moved my WordPress plugin marketplace to a new domain; <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com" title="WordPress plugin marketplace">Extendd.com</a>. I&#8217;m in the process of cleaning up client/users dashboards in the admin area, and had to remove a few menu items that we&#8217;re not necessary for the subscriber role.</p>\n<p>Since subscribers can&#8217;t do anything on the Jetpack page, why should it be there? Here is the snippet I put in my core plugin file to remove Jetpack menu page.</p>\n<pre>\nif ( class_exists( ''Jetpack'' ) &#038;&#038; !current_user_can( ''manage_options'' ) ) {\n	remove_menu_page( ''jetpack'' );\n}\n</pre>\n<p>Just add that into a function that gets called on <code>admin_menu</code> <em>really late</em> like so:</p>\n<pre>\nfunction ap_remove_jetpack_page( ) {\n	if ( class_exists( ''Jetpack'' ) &#038;&#038; !current_user_can( ''manage_options'' ) ) {\n		remove_menu_page( ''jetpack'' );\n	}\n}\nadd_action( ''admin_menu'', ''ap_remove_jetpack_page'', 999 );\n</pre>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/remove-jetpack-menu-page/">Remove Jetpack menu page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/ELQa7IPLjso" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"Extendd core Settings API updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:135:"http://extendd.com/news/extendd-core-settings-api-updated/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=extendd-core-settings-api-updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:510:"<p>If you logged into extendd before 12/2/2012 at 4:00PM PST and downloaded your plugin, you may need to manually download the latest version again. There was a spelling error in the core settings API where it would validate the plugin but show the wrong error. </p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/extendd-core-settings-api-updated/">Extendd core Settings API updated</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"http://extendd.com/?p=6877";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 03 Dec 2012 00:42:08 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1154:"<p>If you logged into extendd before 12/2/2012 at 4:00PM PST and downloaded your plugin, you may need to manually download the latest version again. There was a spelling error in the core settings API where it would validate the plugin but show the wrong error. </p>\n<h4>Custom Login Pro users</h4>\n<p>The settings API was called late and would not show up, there for you can&#8217;t activate your license to receive updates. Please login and download the current version <strong>&gt;</strong> <code>1.2.1</code>.</p>\n<p><strong>A view of the Settings API</strong><br />\n<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://cdn.extendd.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Extendd-Settings-API.png?d3c69e"><img src="http://cdn.extendd.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Extendd-Settings-API-1024x690.png?d3c69e" alt="" title="Extendd Settings API" width="600" height="404" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6879"/></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/extendd-core-settings-api-updated/">Extendd core Settings API updated</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:2:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:36:"\n            \n            \n         ";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:6:"medium";s:5:"image";s:3:"url";s:74:"http://cdn.extendd.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Extendd-Settings-API.png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:2:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"Extendd Settings API";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"thumbnail";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"url";s:82:"http://cdn.extendd.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Extendd-Settings-API-150x101.png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}s:9:"thumbnail";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"url";s:82:"http://cdn.extendd.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Extendd-Settings-API-150x101.png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:77:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"Extendd a new WordPress plugin marketplace";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:153:"http://extendd.com/news/extendd-a-new-wordpress-plugin-marketplace/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=extendd-a-new-wordpress-plugin-marketplace";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:436:"<p>Extendd.com is a premium WordPress marketplace, formally located at thefrosty.com, Extendd adds new plugins and an updated cart system made for easy digital downloads.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/extendd-a-new-wordpress-plugin-marketplace/">Extendd a new WordPress plugin marketplace</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"http://extendd.com/?p=6856";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 02 Dec 2012 06:12:27 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1739:"<p>Welcome to extendd.com (formerly thefrosty.com).</p>\n<h3>Why did I change the domain?</h3>\n<p>No Particular reason, I just felt that TheFrosty was more of a personal site. In fact it was, that was my second domain I ever purchased.</p>\n<h3>Whats new?</h3>\n<p>Extendd is now using a new e-commerce management system: <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://frosty.me/edd">Easy Digital Downloads</a>. I have ported every order over from WooCommerce and as a result all previous license keys have been disabled. If you had an order on the site, you&#8217;ll find your download URLS and licenses on the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/my-account/" title="My Account">My Account</a> page.</p>\n<p class="note">\n<strong>Previous clients</strong><br />\nYou will find a new license key on your account page with a new download link to the <em>latest</em> plugin version of the plugin(s) you purchased. Please download, install and activate the plugin(s) to continue receiving future updates. There is a new settings page where you can activate all plugins by Extendd. I hope this makes it easier.\n</p>\n<h3>Issues</h3>\n<p>If you have any issues please visit the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/support/forum/general/extendd-com/">support forum</a> to report them or bugs you might find on the site and I will fix them as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your previous and continued support! More plugins to come.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/extendd-a-new-wordpress-plugin-marketplace/">Extendd a new WordPress plugin marketplace</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"Announcing Hide &amp; Catch Email Pro and Calendar Date Picker";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:181:"http://extendd.com/news/announcing-hide-catch-email-pro-and-calendar-date-picker/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=announcing-hide-catch-email-pro-and-calendar-date-picker";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:457:"<p>Last week I released Hide and Catch Email Pro, a premium upgrade from the free version in the WordPress repo. I also released Calendar Date Picker today.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/announcing-hide-catch-email-pro-and-calendar-date-picker/">Announcing Hide &#038; Catch Email Pro and Calendar Date Picker</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"http://extendd.com/?p=471";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 20 Nov 2012 20:04:21 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2225:"<p>Last week I released <strong>Hide and Catch Email PRO</strong>, a premium upgrade from the free version you will find in the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/hide-and-catch-email/">WordPress repo</a>. I also released a new plugin today called <strong>Calendar Date Picker</strong>.</p>\n<h2>Hide and Catch Email Pro</h2>\n<p>Hide and Catch Email Pro adds a meta box to all public <code>post_types</code>. When activated the content for that post is hidden behind a form where a user has to submit their email address to see the content.</p>\n<p>Once confirmed the original content is show to the user and a cookie is saved for 30 days so the user doesn&#8217;t have to resubmit the form. The best part, this is all handled by AJAX!</p>\n<h3>Features</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>AJAX form submission.</li>\n<li>Double SPAM protection\n<ul>\n<li>Honey pot field.</li>\n<li>Double form submission. First form sends user a hash key they need to verify.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Submission meta box on each post activated.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Get the plugin <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/product/hide-catch-email-pro/" title="Hide &#038; Catch Email Pro">here</a>.</strong></p>\n<h2>Calendar Date Picker</h2>\n<p>Ever set the wrong date for a post needing to be published in the future at a certain time? Well this plugin hopes to solve that problem. Calendar Date Picker adds the jQuery UI Datepicker and and a custom Timepicker to the edit date dropdown input field.</p>\n<p>The new input field will toggle a full date overlay that when updated to set date and time will update the date input fields. Once you click OK, and OK, the new date is now set and all you have to do is &#8220;schedule&#8221; the post.</p>\n<p><strong>Get the plugin <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/product/calendar-date-picker/" title="Calendar Date Picker">here</a></strong>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/announcing-hide-catch-email-pro-and-calendar-date-picker/">Announcing Hide &#038; Catch Email Pro and Calendar Date Picker</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:46:"Announcing WP Invoice Pro &amp; Ticket Manager";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:149:"http://extendd.com/news/announcing-wp-invoice-pro-ticket-manager/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=announcing-wp-invoice-pro-ticket-manager";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:573:"<p>Last week I quietly released two new plugin on the site. One is the WP Invoice Pro plugin and the other is Ticket Manager. WP Invoice Pro This plugin is for developers or people looking to manage invoices for clients. I&#8217;ve been using a version of this plugin for a few years and thought it [...]</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/announcing-wp-invoice-pro-ticket-manager/">Announcing WP Invoice Pro &#038; Ticket Manager</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"http://extendd.com/?p=409";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 27 Oct 2012 01:31:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2261:"<p>Last week I quietly released two new plugin on the site. One is the WP Invoice Pro plugin and the other is Ticket Manager.</p>\n<h3>WP Invoice Pro</h3>\n<p>This plugin is for developers or people looking to manage invoices for clients. I&#8217;ve been using a version of this plugin for a few years and thought it was time to modify and update the plugin for current WP version and code base. At the same time release it for other to use.</p>\n<p>At the moment <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/product/wordpress-invoice-pro/" title="WordPress Invoice Pro">WP Invoice Pro</a> is in beta testing and is on sale for $5, if you purchase the plugin before final release and full price you will receive the update for free. If you find some bugs or have feature requests leave them in the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/support/forum/wp-invoice-pro/">support forum</a>. Thank you in advance.</p>\n<h4>Known issues with WP Invoice Pro</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Version <code>1.0.0</code> wouldn&#8217;t send the email and had a fatal error, fixed in <code>1.0.1</code>.</li>\n<li>Emails not sending as HTML fixed in <code>1.0.1</code>.</li>\n<li>Shortcodes not finished our outputting yet.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>TODO in WP Invoice Pro final release</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Proper user management/creation with roles. Create client role.</li>\n<li>Built in Quote acceptance callback on emailed or web view quote. Know if then accept or decline the quote with out talking to the client.</li>\n<li>More to come.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Ticket Manager</h2>\n<p>This is a plugin I&#8217;ve been using for the past year on my baseball blog <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://infieldbox.com/">Infield Box</a>. I&#8217;m a Dodgers Season Ticket holder and wanted a easy way to manage tickets I had listed for sale on sites like StubHub etc and what games I could and couldn&#8217;t make.</p>\n<p>This plugin is a simple custom post type with a whole lot of meta fields for ticket info.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com/news/announcing-wp-invoice-pro-ticket-manager/">Announcing WP Invoice Pro &#038; Ticket Manager</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:15;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:77:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"::Krispy Kreme::";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"http://jeanaarter.com/2012/10/krispy-kreme/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:102:"Possibly Related Posts: ::Ignorance:: ::honors:: ::stagecoach prep:: ::besties:: ::life that matters::";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"http://jeanaarter.com/?p=4479";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b: