y scene in the camping area were worth all the stress. I have been looking forward to and talking about&#8230;";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"http://jeanaarter.com/?p=4475";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 13 Oct 2012 12:55:04 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"Entertainment && Fashion";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6285:"<p><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach 2012</a> was my first year, despite the staff stealing my boyfriend&#8217;s tools from his truck and the small camping area, it was a great time. The line up and party scene in the camping area were worth all the stress. I have been looking forward to and talking about <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach 2013</a> since May this year. Needless to say I am incredibly disappointed in the way the organizers of Stagecoach have turned a wonderful event into a retirement party.</p><p>In reality we all should have seen it coming. It is my understanding that during <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach 2011</a> you were able to camp with out your car in a tiny spot. As we all know this changed in 2012. I find it completely unrealistic to require people to fit their car as well as tent in a 10 x 30 area, but hundreds of us did and made the best of the situation. Now for <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach 2013</a> the organizers have upped the anti yet again. For <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach 2013</a> you must own your RV. You cannot even borrow a family member&#8217;s if you have the same last name (I asked). To add insult to injury you still have to apply and be approved to purchase the $850 or $950 RV spot for the weekend! If you want to camp, well have fun finding an off site rental and paying $100 for a shuttle.</p><p>On Tuesday October 9th, when the lineup and new rules were announced I contacted <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach</a> via email.</p><blockquote><p> A lot of people are confused as to where we are suppose to stay.</p><p>We can only purchase an RV spot if we personally own the RV. We are not allowed to borrow a family RV.<br\n /> And there is no car/tent camping this year?</p><p>There is no way the hotels can accommodate the number of people who camped last year alone.</p><p>Jeana Arter, M.A.</p></blockquote><p>My main thought process was this, if <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach</a> has sold out in past years, camping and RV spots, surrounding hotels have also sold out where do the organizers think everyone will stay?</p><p>Their solution/response:</p><blockquote><p> You can check out some of the offsite campgrounds:</p><p>http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/visitors/offsite-camping</p><p>or Hotels</p><p>http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/visitors/hotels</p><p>There are several thousands of people that attend the festival and do not<br\n /> camp on site. We also have a couple other festivals with several thousand<br\n /> more attendees than Stagecoach that also do not camp on site.</p><p>We are primarily a Country Music Festival not a camping event. This<br\n /> particular year, for 2013, we are trying a more intimate camping<br\n /> experience.</p><p>We really do hope you can still make it.</p><p>Whomever responded to my email wanted to clarify that href=&#8221;http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/&#8221; title=&#8221;Stagecoach&#8221; target=&#8221;_blank&#8221;&gt;Stagecoach is a country music festival. Thanks, as if I am so stupid I did not comprehend the purpose of camping in 100+ degree temperatures for four days. I was really annoyed by this and decided to tell them.</p><blockquote><p> I will be sure to pass along your overly accommodating response to my group of twenty plus who planned on attending again this year.</p><p>I am aware thousands attended the festival last year and did not camp. My point was simply how do you expect surrounding venues to accommodate additional attendees if all hotels were sold out last year?</p><p>You could have at least been honest in your response. In 2013 you are targeting an older demographic. This is made clear by the line up and by requiring individuals to own the RV. Mean while looking to maximize your profit via RV rentals, $1000 per weekend, compared to car camping $100 per weekend.</p><p>Thank you for clarifying that Stagecoach is a music festival.</p><p>Jeana<br\n /> Sent from my iPhone</p></blockquote><p>I am more frustrated by the <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/Stagecoach" title="Stagecoach Twitter">Stagecoach Twitter</a> account retweeting all the positive tweets but ignoring the negative ones. I understand not everyone is tactful on twitter, especially when angry. However, I personally have sent constructive feedback and been ignored. Newsflash <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.stagecoachfestival.com/" title="Stagecoach">Stagecoach</a>, just because you ignore the problem does not mean people will forget.</p><p>To be honest, I was not expecting a response to my email after my tweets went and remain unanswered. So to their credit at least feedback is being read. So send in your emails people. Do not just sit back and rant on twitter, contact the organizers. I hope that all those who claim to be boycotting this year actually follow through. This will be the only way that any change will be possible in the future.</p><p>More importantly, I hope <a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://www.countrythunder.com/" title="Country Thunder">Country Thunder</a> is ready for an new attendees!</p></blockquote><div\n id="related"><h4>Possibly Related Posts:</h4><ul><li><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://jeanaarter.com/2012/02/love-this/">:love this::</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://jeanaarter.com/2012/01/love-them/">::love them::</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://jeanaarter.com/2012/01/conference-dress/">::conference dress::</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://jeanaarter.com/2012/01/perfection/">::perfection::</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow"\n target="_blank" href="http://jeanaarter.com/2012/01/interview-attire/">::interview attire::</a></li></ul></div><br\n />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:17;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"Updated: List all Multisite blogs in the WordPress admin bar";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AustinPassy/~3/F9TdxgqWYqE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:369:"<p>List all WordPress multisite blogs in the WP admin bar.</p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/list-all-multisite-blogs-in-the-wordpress-admin-bar/">Updated: List all Multisite blogs in the WordPress admin bar</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://austinpassy.com/?p=2637";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 20 Sep 2012 04:29:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3544:"<p>Recently I&#8217;ve been working on some theme&#8217;s to list either on my <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://thefrosty.com">frosty</a> site, or <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://themeforest.net/user/austyfrosty?ref=austyfrosty">themeforest</a>. In order to do so I had to modify an old demo&#8217;s theme site that was on a previous domain I let go.</p>\n<p>So here is the class I built to list all sites:</p>\n<pre>\nclass the_frosty_network {\n	\n	const version	= ''0.3.1'';\n	\n	function __construct() {		\n		add_action( ''admin_bar_menu'', array( $this, ''adminbar'' ), 99 );\n		add_filter( ''show_admin_bar'', ''__return_true'', 1000 );\n	}\n	\n	function adminbar( $wp_admin_bar ) {\n		if ( !is_user_logged_in() ) {\n			\n    		$wp_admin_bar-&gt;add_node( array(\n				''id'' =&gt; ''sites'', ''title'' =&gt; __( ''Sites'' )\n			) );\n			\n			$this-&gt;adminbar_sites( $wp_admin_bar );\n		}		\n	}\n	\n	/**\n	 * If is_multisite() query the database for all sites\n	 * then cache the query and output the site''s details\n	 *\n	 */\n	function adminbar_sites( $wp_admin_bar ) {\n		\n		if ( !is_multisite() ) return;\n		\n		global $wpdb;\n		\n		/* http://codex.wordpress.org/WPMU_Functions/get_site_option */\n		$cache = sanitize_title_with_dashes( get_site_option( ''site_name'' ) ) . ''_sites'';\n		\n		/* http://codex.wordpress.org/Class_Reference/WP_Object_Cache */\n		$blogs = wp_cache_get( $cache );\n		\n		if ( false === $blogs ) {\n			$blogs = $wpdb-&gt;get_results(\n				"SELECT blog_id\n				FROM {$wpdb-&gt;blogs}\n				WHERE site_id = ''{$wpdb-&gt;siteid}''\n				AND spam = ''0''\n				AND deleted = ''0''\n				AND archived = ''0''\n				AND public = ''1''\n				AND blog_id != 1"\n			);\n			wp_cache_set( $cache, $result );\n		\n			//print_r( $blogs );\n			\n			if ( empty( $blogs ) ) return;\n			wp_cache_set( $cache, $blogs );\n		}\n	\n		$sites = array();\n		\n		foreach ( $blogs as $blog ) {\n			$sites[$blog-&gt;blog_id] = get_blog_details( $blog-&gt;blog_id, ''blogname'' );\n		}\n		\n		//print_r( $sites );\n		\n		foreach ( $sites as $blog_id =&gt; $site ) {\n			$wp_admin_bar-&gt;add_node( array(\n				''parent'' =&gt; ''sites'',\n				''id'' =&gt; ''site-'' . $site-&gt;blog_id,\n				''title'' =&gt; $site-&gt;blogname,\n				''href'' =&gt; $site-&gt;siteurl\n			) );\n		}\n	}\n	\n};\nadd_action( ''plugins_loaded'', create_function( '''', ''new the_frosty_network;'' ), 9 );\n\n</pre>\n<p>For a working preview, check out <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://demo.thefrosty.com">demo.thefrosty.com</a>, else check out the images below:</p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/wp-admin-bar-list-sites.png"><img src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/wp-admin-bar-list-sites.png" alt="" title="wp-admin-bar-list-sites" width="900" height="600" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2638"/></a></p>\n<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/wp-admin-bar-list-sites-down.png"><img src="http://cdn.austinpassy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/wp-admin-bar-list-sites-down.png" alt="" title="wp-admin-bar-list-sites-down" width="900" height="600" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2639"/></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com/tutorials/list-all-multisite-blogs-in-the-wordpress-admin-bar/">Updated: List all Multisite blogs in the WordPress admin bar</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://austinpassy.com">Austin Passy</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/F9TdxgqWYqE" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:18;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n         \n      ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"After Party Details";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordCampLA/~3/5uwZYAAkFqM/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"Afterparty @ Brennans Pub (map) 4089 Lincoln Blvd, Marina del Rey, California";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"http://2012.la.wordcamp.org/?p=1080";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 15 Sep 2012 23:01:09 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1289:"<p>Afterparty @ Brennans Pub 