(19, 1, '2012-12-06 04:33:34', '2012-12-06 04:33:34', 'Enacted in 1977 as the Targeted Job Tax Credit (PL 95-30), this Act was renewed in 1996 by the Work Opportunity Tax Credit Act. (PL 104-188).  The Act reward companies for hiring “economically disadvantaged” and “hard to hire” individuals. \r\nAny business can earn WOTC tax credits by hiring individuals who fit one of the program’s target groups such as veterans, disabled persons and persons who have received food stamps. \r\n\r\nNewly hired employees are screened to see if they qualify. If they do, employers can earn up to $9,600 in federal tax credits per employee. WOTC income tax credits can be applied quarterly and annually against federal income tax liability and unused credits can be carried forward 20 years, or carried back 1 year (IRC  Sec. 39).\r\n\r\n<h4>We help you maximize the tax credits you deserve when you hire those who need it the most.</h4>', 'Work Opportunity Tax Credit (WOTC)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'work-opportunity-tax-credit-wotc', '', '', '2012-12-25 21:40:02', '2012-12-25 21:40:02', '', 42, 'http://10.0.1.22:8888/fcci/?page_id=19', 1, 'page', '', 0),
