(39, 1, '2012-12-06 04:44:48', '2012-12-06 04:44:48', '<h2>Overview</h2>\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting, Inc. professionals have decades of experience working with financial\r\ninstitutions. Our insight and understanding of financial institution''s lending practices, financial\r\nreporting, regulatory hurdles, compliance issues, and operational knowledge comes from one of\r\nits key members, who serve as a board member of a large regional bank''s loan, asset/liability,\r\nand compliance committees. Such inside knowledge of financial institutions is enhanced with\r\nother professionals, who have provided credits and incentives services to national banking\r\ninstitutions for decades at the "Big 4" accounting firms.\r\n\r\n<h2>Company Profile</h2>\r\nA multi-billion dollar regional bank established in 1980, to serve small to mid-sized businesses\r\nacross the U.S. Like most banks, in 2008, the bank’s loan loss reserve ballooned, the earnings\r\nturned negative and total asset decreased.\r\n\r\n<h2>Tax Savings</h2>\r\nWith inside working knowledge of financial institutions, First Capitol Consulting, Inc. represented\r\na bank in an audit with the California Franchise Tax Board. With our keen understanding\r\nof lending practices and financial regulatory rules, we preserved the bank''s $56 million net\r\ninterest deduction and tax credit amount in excess of $560,000 per annum, thus increasing its\r\nshareholder value by increasing its ROI and ROA.\r\nSubsequently, the bank turned the financial corner to profitability without resorting to the federal\r\nTARP assistance in 2011.', 'Banks and National Financial Institutions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'banks-and-national-financial-institutions', '', '', '2012-12-25 22:57:22', '2012-12-25 22:57:22', '', 37, 'http://10.0.1.22:8888/fcci/?page_id=39', 1, 'page', '', 0),
