(132, 1, '2012-12-06 19:57:46', '2012-12-06 19:57:46', 'Our WOTC questionnaire is imbedded in to client’s web employee application. All screened candidates will be screened automatically via TaxAdvantage<sup>sm</sup> for WOTC qualification.<img alt="process-online" src="http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/process-online.png" width="630" /><ol>\r\n	<li>Applicant applies for a position via the client''s electronic process (kiosk or online) and TaxAdvantagesm presents the eligibility questions from within the client’s e-process.</li>\r\n	<li>HR Manager makes and records hiring decision within client’s e-process.</li>\r\n	<li>TaxAdvantage<sup>sm</sup> creates eligibility and pre-populated forms for eligible new hires.</li>\r\n	<li>HR Manager obtains new hire’s signature on the forms and mails them to First Capitol.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h4>The Online Process: Benefits</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Efficient integration into e-process hiring</li>\r\n<li>All employees are entered into the TaxAdvantagesm system for analysis</li>\r\n<li>8850 forms are auto generated and printable</li>\r\n<li>Data is available immediately</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Online Web Integrated', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'online-web-integrated', '', '', '2012-12-29 18:41:34', '2012-12-29 18:41:34', '', 112, 'http://10.0.1.22:8888/fcci/?page_id=132', 3, 'page', '', 0),
(133, 1, '2012-12-06 19:57:22', '2012-12-06 19:57:22', 'Our WOTC questionnaire is imbedded in to client’s web employee application. All screened candidates will be screened automatically via TaxAdvantagesm for WOTC qualification.\n\nApplicant applies for a position via the client’s electronic process (kiosk or online) and TaxAdvantagesm presents the eligibility questions from within the client’s e-process.\nHR Manager makes and records hiring decision within client’s e-process.\nTaxAdvantage<sup>sm</sup> creates eligibility and pre-populated forms for eligible new hires.\nHR Manager obtains new hire’s signature on the forms and mails them to First Capitol.', 'Online Web Integrated', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision', '', '', '2012-12-06 19:57:22', '2012-12-06 19:57:22', '', 132, 'http://10.0.1.22:8888/fcci/132-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting professionals have decades of experience working with financial institutions.  First Capitol Consulting insight and understanding of financial institution’s lending practices, financial reporting, regulatory hurdles, compliance issues, and operational knowledge comes from one of its key members, who serve as a board member of a large regional bank’s loan, asset/liability, and compliance committees.  Such inside knowledge of financial institution is enhanced with other professionals, who have provided credits and incentives services to national banking institutions for decades at the “Big 4” accounting firms.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA multi-billion regional bank, established in 1980, to serve small to mid-sized businesses across the U.S.  Like most banks, in 2008, the bank’s loan loss reserve ballooned, the earnings turned negative and total asset decreased.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nWith inside working knowledge of financial institutions, First Capitol Consulting represented the bank in an audit with the California Franchise Tax Board.  First Capitol Consulting, with its keen understanding of lending practices and financial regulatory rules, preserved the bank’s $56 million net interest deduction and tax credit amount in excess of $560,000 per annum - increasing its shareholder value by increasing its ROI and ROA.  \r\n\r\nThe bank in 2011 turned the financial corner to profitability without resorting to the federal TARP assistance.', 'Banks and National Financial Institutions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-revision-4', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '', 39, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/39-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2012-12-11 05:35:05', '2012-12-11 05:35:05', '<h2>Overview</h2>\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting professionals have decades of experience working with financial institutions.  First Capitol Consulting insight and understanding of financial institution’s lending practices, financial reporting, regulatory hurdles, compliance issues, and operational knowledge comes from one of its key members, who serve as a board member of a large regional bank’s loan, asset/liability, and compliance committees.  Such inside knowledge of financial institution is enhanced with other professionals, who have provided credits and incentives services to national banking institutions for decades at the “Big 4” accounting firms.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA multi-billion regional bank, established in 1980, to serve small to mid-sized businesses across the U.S.  Like most banks, in 2008, the bank’s loan loss reserve ballooned, the earnings turned negative and total asset decreased.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nWith inside working knowledge of financial institutions, First Capitol Consulting represented the bank in an audit with the California Franchise Tax Board.  First Capitol Consulting, with its keen understanding of lending practices and financial regulatory rules, preserved the bank’s $56 million net interest deduction and tax credit amount in excess of $560,000 per annum - increasing its shareholder value by increasing its ROI and ROA.  \r\n\r\nThe bank in 2011 turned the financial corner to profitability without resorting to the federal TARP assistance.', 'Banks and National Financial Institutions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-revision-5', '', '', '2012-12-11 05:35:05', '2012-12-11 05:35:05', '', 39, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/39-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting, consisting of lawyers, CPAs and tax professionals, have developed strong relationships with the taxing authorities by producing the highest quality work and being recognized as the industry experts.  First Capitol Consulting has represented companies in audits, appeals, settlements and hearings.  By doing so, First Capitol Consulting demonstrated its expertise and is  recognized as the industry leader.  \r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA manufacturer with an annual gross sale of $150 million per annum.  During its exam, $1,2 million tax credits, generated by credits and incentives company with no licensed individual, were denied by the auditor.  \r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nThe company contacted First Capitol Consulting to assist with its audit.  First Capitol Consulting represented the company and generated over $2.5 million in tax credits to offset any disallowed tax credits and increase its refunds.', 'IRS and State Taxing Authorities Represenation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '85-revision-2', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '', 85, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/85-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(137, 1, '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting developed TaxAdvantagesm with Intuit to serve 1.4 million small to mid-sized companies.  Its working knowledge of small to mid-sized businesses is unparalleled in the industry.  First Capitol Consulting understands the needs and limited resources of small to mid-sized companies.  Hence, First Capitol Consulting implementation process requires very limited participation by its clients. \r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA small apparel manufacturer established in 1971 with 30 employees.  Although lost many major retail clients, the company started to establish itself back in the market place by creating innovative fashion design.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nA First Capitol Consulting’s account executive, who specializes in small to mid-sized companies, deployed single point of contact with the company.  Utilizing First Capitol Consulting’s vast network of CPAs and payroll companies, First Capitol Consulting obtained refunds in excess of $200,000, a much needed cash infusion to the company as it needed capital to build inventory based on its new fashion designs.', 'Small & Mid-Sized Businesss', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '87-revision-3', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '2012-12-06 18:01:03', '', 87, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/87-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(138, 1, '2012-12-06 18:02:07', '2012-12-06 18:02:07', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting understands the workings and needs of high-tech companies.  First Capitol Consulting, in a partnership with Intuit, developed its proprietary software and its web-portal.  First Capitol Consulting understands the high-tech company inititiatives, personnel and very specific needs.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nIndustry leader and Fortune 500 company, expanding to other states and countries.  Due to its rapid growth, the company utilized temp work source for growth.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting’s understanding of high-tech company operations and hiring practices led to capturing tax credits that were previously overlooked by other credits and incentive providers.  By implementing its strategy, First Capitol Consulting increased federal credits and quadrupled state tax credits.', 'High – Tech Companies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '89-revision-2', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:02:07', '2012-12-06 18:02:07', '', 89, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/89-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting understands the workings and needs retail companies.  Our TaxAdvantagesm web-portal, call center and technology was developed to handle over 1.4 million companies with unlimited number of employees and locations.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA retail company with over 213 locations.  All hiring done locally at the retail site.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting utilized its call-center, payroll integration, “best practices” webinars, quarterly management meetings and weekly compliance report to accomplish 97% WOTC compliance result.', 'Retail', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '91-revision-2', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '', 91, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/91-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting has strong prescence in automotive industry.  First Capitol Consulting currently works with an automotive company with over 1.2 billion in assets.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nAs one of the fastest growing automotive company in the country, the company needed assistance with federal tax credit programs.  \r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting utilized its call-center and web integrated portal to capture federal tax credits.  First Capitol Consulting process resulted in 47% increase in hiring tax credit compared to previously completed by a publicly traded tax credit company.', 'Automative', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '93-revision-2', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '', 93, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/93-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting currently represents over 3,000 franchise chain restaurants in the U.S.  First Capitol Consulting works very closely with payroll companies to accomplish high compliance rate and has deep understanding of employee scheduling complexities.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nSalt Lake City, Utah based fast food chain operator with rapid growth in Texas and Nevada.  The company acquired over 30 locations per annum.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting utilized its call-center, payroll integration, “best practices” webinars, quarterly management meetings and weekly compliance report to accomplish 92% WOTC compliance result.  This is in light of the company with 300% turnover per annum.', 'Franchise Chain Restaurants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-5', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '', 95, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/95-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(142, 1, '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting understands the workings and needs transportation companies.  Our TaxAdvantagesm web-portal, call center and technology was developed to handle over 1.4 million companies with unlimited number of employees and locations.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nA transportation company with over 86 locations.  All hiring done locally at the retail site with a centralized HR.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting utilized its call-center, web integration, and pre-screening to meet the needs of the hiring with 40% turnover per annum.', 'Transportation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-3', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '2012-12-06 18:03:06', '', 97, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/97-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(143, 1, '2012-12-06 18:02:04', '2012-12-06 18:02:04', 'Overview\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting, with tax professionals from the “Big 4’ accounting firms, understands, not just credits and incentives, but intricacies and pit-falls of merging two national brands.  First Capitol Consulting assisted merger of one of the oldest cosmetic companies in the world.\r\n\r\nCompany Profile\r\n\r\nIndustry leader and well recognized national brand in cosmetics acquired by a foreign international company.\r\n\r\nTax Savings\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting, with its professionals with deep roots in mergers and acquisitions, assisted the acquired company and the shareholders to tax minimization.  ', 'Cosmetic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '99-revision-3', '', '', '2012-12-06 18:02:04', '2012-12-06 18:02:04', '', 99, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/99-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
