(232, 1, '2012-12-18 05:56:09', '2012-12-18 05:56:09', 'Our call-center, located here in Los Angeles, is operated by highly specialized staff who are trained to identify for WOTC and other screening credits.  Moreover, our staff will answer up-to-date status of the certification process and communicate directly with the local state workforce agencies to resolve any screening credits related issues pertaining to additional documentation needs as well as repeal or contest factual and technical issues.  To ensure proper certification of qualified employee, our call center professionals are responsible for the following:\r\n\r\nOnce the questionnaire is completed utilizing one of the four methods, the Forms 9061 and 8850 are auto-generated for each interviewed employee.  9061, 8850 and supporting documentation are scanned and digitally stored.  Originals are sent by First Capitol to their respective state agencies \r\n\r\nAll certificates are mailed via certified mail or FedEx to ensure that the 28 day deadline is met. Currently, the certification process takes from 2 months to 2 years, depending on the jurisdiction.  Certification documents are also digitally stored upon receipt.  \r\n\r\nIf certification is denied, First Capitol will appeal when appropriate.  In certain instances, an employee may qualify for more than one criterion. If additional documentation is requested by a certifying agency, First Capitol will collect and transmit as necessary.  \r\n\r\nWhen an employee is certified, the corresponding client’s account is updated to reflect the possibility of the individual actually generating credits.  Periodic payroll reports are used to calculate actual credit amounts, and invoiced at the time of application.', 'Toll Free Call Center Support', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'toll-free-call-center-support', '', '', '2012-12-27 04:44:38', '2012-12-27 04:44:38', '', 107, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/?page_id=232', 5, 'page', '', 0),
