(264, 1, '2012-12-18 06:16:51', '2012-12-18 06:16:51', 'A tax credit differs from a tax deduction. A tax deduction lowers the amount of income subject to taxation. A tax credit, however, lowers the amount of tax owed directly.\r\n\r\nCredits result in a dollar-for-dollar reduction in actual tax liability, which makes them much more valuable than deductions. A tax refund is what you receive when you’ve already paid too much tax and the government returns the amount that you’ve overpaid. ', 'What is a tax deduction, a tax credit and a tax refund?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-a-tax-deduction-a-tax-credit-and-a-tax-refund', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:16:51', '2012-12-18 06:16:51', '', 0, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/?post_type=faqs&#038;p=264', 3, 'faqs', '', 0),
