(266, 1, '2012-12-18 06:17:27', '2012-12-18 06:17:27', 'Working with tax incentive programs such as CAEZ and WOTC requires specialized expertise. The CAEZ has geographic constraints to eligibility. General accountants lack specialized expertise to implement these programs for their clients.\r\n\r\nWOTC, unlike the CAEZ, does not have geographic constraints. However, for each qualifying employee, there is only a window of 28 days within which to satisfy the myriad of requirements and submit all necessary documents to the IRS. Properly implementing the WOTC requires constant attention and maintenance. General accounting firms do not have the resources necessary to constantly monitor the entire process.', 'Doesn''t my CPA/accountant already implement CAEZ and WOTC savings for me? Why not?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'doesnt-my-cpaaccountant-already-implement-caez-and-wotc-savings-for-me-why-not', '', '', '2012-12-26 01:47:45', '2012-12-26 01:47:45', '', 0, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/?post_type=faqs&#038;p=266', 4, 'faqs', '', 0);
