(268, 1, '2012-12-18 06:17:27', '2012-12-18 06:17:27', 'Working with tax incentive programs such as CAEZ and WOTC requires specialized expertise.  The CAEZ has geographic constraints to eligibility. General accounting lack specialized expertise to implement these programs for their clients.\r\n\r\nWOTC, unlike the CAEZ, does not have geographic constraints. However, for each qualifying employee, there is only a window of 28 days within which to satisfy the myriad requirements and submit all necessary documents to the IRS. Properly implementing the WOTC requires constant attention and maintenance. General accounting firms do not have the resources necessary to constantly monitor the entire process', 'Doesn''t my CPA/accountant already implement CAEZ and WOTC savings for me? Why not?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '266-revision-2', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:17:27', '2012-12-18 06:17:27', '', 266, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/266-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(269, 1, '2012-12-18 06:17:43', '2012-12-18 06:17:43', 'If your business is a LLC, S-Corporation, partnership or sole proprietorship, then you personally may be entitled to tax refunds and future tax savings through these programs. C-Corporations can have their business taxes reduced and refunded. ', 'How does it benefit me?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-does-it-benefit-me', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:17:43', '2012-12-18 06:17:43', '', 0, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/?post_type=faqs&#038;p=269', 5, 'faqs', '', 0),
