(338, 1, '2012-12-23 19:19:24', '2012-12-23 19:19:24', '<h2>Overview</h2>\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting professionals have decades of experience working with financial institutions.  First Capitol Consulting insight and understanding of financial institution’s lending practices, financial reporting, regulatory hurdles, compliance issues, and operational knowledge comes from one of its key members, who serve as a board member of a large regional bank’s loan, asset/liability, and compliance committees.  Such inside knowledge of financial institution is enhanced with other professionals, who have provided credits and incentives services to national banking institutions for decades at the “Big 4” accounting firms.\r\n\r\n<h2>Company Profile</h2>\r\n\r\nA multi-billion regional bank, established in 1980, to serve small to mid-sized businesses across the U.S.  Like most banks, in 2008, the bank’s loan loss reserve ballooned, the earnings turned negative and total asset decreased.\r\n\r\n<h2>Tax Savings</h2>\r\n\r\nWith inside working knowledge of financial institutions, First Capitol Consulting represented the bank in an audit with the California Franchise Tax Board.  First Capitol Consulting, with its keen understanding of lending practices and financial regulatory rules, preserved the bank’s $56 million net interest deduction and tax credit amount in excess of $560,000 per annum - increasing its shareholder value by increasing its ROI and ROA.  \r\n\r\nThe bank in 2011 turned the financial corner to profitability without resorting to the federal TARP assistance.', 'Banks and National Financial Institutions', 'First Capitol Consulting professionals have decades of experience working with financial institutions.  First Capitol Consulting insight and understanding of financial institution’s lending practices, financial reporting, regulatory hurdles, compliance issues, and operational knowledge', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'banks-and-national-financial-institutions', 