(538, 1, '2012-12-06 04:58:56', '2012-12-06 04:58:56', 'Enacted in 1977 as the Targeted Job Tax Credit (PL 95-30), this Act was renewed in 1996 by the Work Opportunity Tax Credit Act. (PL 104-188).  The Act reward companies for hiring “economically disadvantaged” and “hard to hire” individuals. \r\nAny business can earn WOTC tax credits by hiring individuals who fit one of the program’s target groups such as veterans, disabled persons and persons who have received food stamps. \r\n\r\nNewly hired employees are screened to see if they qualify. If they do, employers can earn up to $9,600 in federal tax credits per employee. WOTC income tax credits can be applied quarterly and annually against federal income tax liability and unused credits can be carried forward 20 years, or carried back 1 year (IRC  Sec. 39).\r\n\r\nWe help you maximize the tax credits you deserve when you hire those who need it the most.', 'Work Opportunity Tax Credit (WOTC)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '19-revision-4', '', '', '2012-12-06 04:58:56', '2012-12-06 04:58:56', '', 19, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/19-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(539, 1, '2012-12-06 17:36:34', '2012-12-06 17:36:34', 'First Capitol Consulting consists of tax professionals from the “Big 4” accounting firms.  Our TaxAdvantagesm was developed in a partnership with Intuit to serve  1.4 million clients with unlimited number of employees to provide our credits and incentives services.  Currently, First Capitol is in a strategic partnership with McGladrey and is the preferred WOTC service provider of Grant Thornton.  First Capitol Consulting is recognized as the industry leader in every aspect: reputation, performance, audit, experience and expertise. ', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-5', '', '', '2012-12-06 17:36:34', '2012-12-06 17:36:34', '', 9, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/9-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
