(572, 1, '2012-12-18 03:03:25', '2012-12-18 03:03:25', 'First Capitol Consulting offers four methods of WOTC screening: paper filing, toll-free call center, on-line web integrated and direct web access.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Paper Filing</li>\r\n	<li>Toll-Free Call Center</li>\r\n	<li>Online Web Integrated</li>\r\n	<li>Web-in Direct</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Four Delivery Methods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '112-revision-3', '', '', '2012-12-18 03:03:25', '2012-12-18 03:03:25', '', 112, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/112-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(573, 1, '2012-12-25 22:42:49', '2012-12-25 22:42:49', '<img src="http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/process-overall.png" alt="process-overall" width="630"/>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>We collect all the necessary documents for your business, Federal and State.</li>\r\n	<li>We do all the required paperwork.</li>\r\n	<li>No upfront or hidden costs.</li>\r\n	<li>We work directly with your tax preparer to deliver the information you need to use these tax credits.</li>\r\n	<li>You save money on your taxes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n*We guarantee any and all credits accumulated through our work. We represent you in the case of an audit, unlike payroll companies and other competitors.', 'Overall Process', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '110-revision-3', '', '', '2012-12-25 22:42:49', '2012-12-25 22:42:49', '', 110, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/110-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(574, 1, '2012-12-18 06:05:44', '2012-12-18 06:05:44', 'Developed in partnership with Intuit, TaxAdvantagesm is “cloud” computing that allows real-time access to work produced. First Capitol guarantees timely completion of work, business hour accessibility for information and if needed, audit representation.\r\n\r\nImplementation of WOTC requires handling and maintaining secret, sensitive and restrictive personal and confidential information.  To insure protection of confidential and private information, First Capitol has in place the following policies and procedures:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="#hr-policies">Human Resource Policies</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#it-policies">Information Technology Policies and Procedures</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#bca-plan">Business Continuity Assurance Plan</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name="hr-policies"></a>\r\n<h2>HUMAN RESOURCE POLICIES</h2>\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol sets high standards for the company’s employees and officers that establish the foundation for the management team’s philosophy and operation style that reinforces the importance of sound corporate governance.  To that end, First Capitol has formal personnel policies and procedures addressing screening, hiring, transfers, and employee termination.  Organization structure and job descriptions define an employee’s assigned responsibilities and lines of authority of reporting.  Throughout the hiring process, our intensive screening increases the assurance that potential employees are qualified for the responsibilities of their positions.  Offers of employment are contingent on the satisfactory completion of pre-employment background screening.  \r\n\r\nA new hire checklist is used to confirm that the required standard employment documentation is collected for new hires.  As a condition of employment, employees are required to acknowledge in writing that they have received copies of the Employee Handbook, read it, and understand that the Employee Handbook contains First Capitol’s expectations regarding conduct in the business environment.  Employees also must sign a non-disclosure and confidentiality agreements to protect the intellectual property of First Capitol and the confidential information of its customers.\r\n\r\n<a name="it-policies"></a>\r\n<h2>INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY POLICIES AND PROCEDURES</h2>\r\n\r\nAs a part of management practice, First Capitol has established policies and procedures for Information Technology (“IT”).  First Capitol IT policies and procedures set standards for operating and maintaining the stability, security, controls and functionality of all technology elements, data, and associated services.  Our policies and procedures are designed to meet the regulatory expectations set forth by SAS 70/SASE 16/SOC 2 requirements.\r\n\r\n<a name="bca-plan"></a>\r\n<h2>BUSINESS CONTINUITY ASSURANCE PLAN (“BCAP”)</h2>\r\n\r\nFirst Capitol BCAP ensures the efficient and effective resumption of the identified critical function of First Capitol in the event of a disaster.  The primary goal of BCAP is to provide the roadmap for the recovery of services provided by First Capitol during an extended interruption or outage.  First Capitol has in place defined organization, infrastructure, resources, processes and procedures necessary to support the effective and efficient restoration and recovery of critical business processes, computer, and data network resources. ', 'Technology and Data Security', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '184-revision-6', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:05:44', '2012-12-18 06:05:44', '', 184, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/184-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(575, 1, '2012-12-25 22:50:36', '2012-12-25 22:50:36', '<img src="http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/partnerships-cpa-accounting.png" alt="partnerships-cpa-accounting" width="630" />First Capitol Consulting works with accountants and CPA''s to provide tax credit and incentive benefits to your clients. \r\n\r\nFirst Capitol Consulting can pre-screen your clients according to their business addresses to verify if they are eligible for state and/or federal tax credits. For your clients who are eligible, our proprietary TaxAdvantage<sup>SM</sup> software will allow us to accurately calculate tax credits, prepare all necessary forms and give you all the information you need to prepare your clients'' tax returns in a timely and transparent manner. Working with First Capitol Consulting will allow you to save your clients thousands of dollars and gain additional revenue. \r\n\r\nBenefits to CPA and Accounting Firms\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Retain clients</li>\r\n<li>Gain additional revenue</li> \r\n<li>Gain new clients</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nBenefits to Clients\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Recover capital</li>\r\n<li>Reduce tax liabilities</li>\r\n<li>Raise profits</li>\r\n</ul>', 'CPA & accounting firms', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '190-revision-7', '', '', '2012-12-25 22:50:36', '2012-12-25 22:50:36', '', 190, 'http://10.0.1.19:8888/fcci/190-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
